<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is basically the deck I&#39;ve played in 75% of my online tournaments after Mount Doom. It has been through a lot of changes, especially the threats stuff for the southrons.<br />
Think my run with it is about 35-5 or something like that (including 3 PSQs). <br />
I have lost count of the times I have played Desert Lord, SL and a Mumak at Cavern Entrance site 2. That&#39;s 11 twilight of pain ;)<br />
<br />
The decks main weakness is obviously knights. Unless I use Grima/Sarumans Power they are an autoloss. With G/SP you&#39;re weaker against most other decks, and slightly better vs knights.<br />
Bad draws is also a pain in the ass. Especially with this deck. Considering I only use 15 minions, it is important that these are relativly evenly distributed throughout the deck.<br />
<br />
The reason I&#39;m posting it is the upcoming rotation, and I wanted to post a good deck here.   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
